# ObsidianAI — Cursor Project Rules (Updated April 2026)

## The ONE production site
- index.html at ROOT = obsidianai.org (GitHub Pages, root branch)
- style.css = complete design system, do not restructure
- script.js = complete JS including Stripe audit flow and chat widget
- legacy-static/ = DELETED, do not reference
- Old HTML pages (solutions.html, pricing.html, roadmap.html, contact.html) = DELETED

## Backend
- app.py = FastAPI on Render at https://obsidianai-evtu.onrender.com
- Has: /chat, /health, /create-payment-intent, /stripe-webhook, /upload-report, /clients
- agent.py = ObsidianAgent (xAI Grok)
- grok-mcp/server.js = MCP server for Cursor, should be connected

## Next.js app (/web directory)
- Status: built, NOT deployed, experimental
- Design: different aesthetic (zinc/cyan glassmorphism, Geist font, Framer Motion)
- Decision: keep as v2 experiment for Q2 client portal build
- Do NOT deploy /web until $97 audit is ported into it

## Critical pending items
1. STRIPE KEY — script.js line ~82 has pk_live_YOUR_KEY_HERE, replace with real key
2. RENDER ENV VARS — add STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, RESEND_API_KEY
3. UPTIMEROBOT — ping /health every 5 min to prevent Render cold start
4. OG IMAGE — run generate_og.py, commit og-image.png

## Design system (never change)
- Background #000, text #fff, border #181818
- Green #4ade80 success only, Amber #fbbf24 warning only
- Fonts: Syne display, DM Mono mono
- No gradients, no shadows except chat widget, max border-radius 3px

## Revenue priority
1. Stripe activation → $97 audits → first $97
2. First Core client signed → $35,940 ARR
3. Client portal (Node.js, Q2)
4. Obsidian Sentry autonomous SOC (Q3)
